###  https://www.michaeldebellis.com/docs/Advertising_Revenue_By_Age_Segment_Report_2025
docs:Advertising_Revenue_By_Age_Segment_Report_2025 rdf:type owl:NamedIndividual ,
                                                             docs:Report ;
                                                    docs:chunk_text """Advertising Revenue by Age Segment (Last 12 Months 2025)

| Age Segment | Ad Revenue (USD) | % of Total |
|------------|------------------:|-----------:|
| Under_18   |      8,000,000    |       4%   |
| 18_34      |     92,000,000    |      46%   |
| 35_54      |     76,000,000    |      38%   |
| 55_plus    |     24,000,000    |      12%   |

Notes:
- 18–34 is the largest revenue contributor.
- 35–54 is a close second and may have higher revenue per user.
"""@en .


###  https://www.michaeldebellis.com/docs/Creator_Engagement_Report_Q3_2025
docs:Creator_Engagement_Report_Q3_2025 rdf:type owl:NamedIndividual ,
                                                docs:Quarterly_Report ;
                                       docs:uses_data_product dp:SF_Creator_Insights_Product ,
                                                              dp:SF_Video_Metadata_Product ;
                                       docs:uses_dataset <https://www.michaeldebellis.com/streamforge/dataset/Creator_Engagement_Metrics> ,
                                                         <https://www.michaeldebellis.com/streamforge/dataset/Video_Metadata_Current> ;
                                       dcterms:created "2025-10-10"^^xsd:date ;
                                       dcterms:creator "Creator Growth Analytics Team"@en ;
                                       dcterms:publisher "StreamForge Data Products Group"@en ;
                                       dcterms:title "Creator Engagement Report — Q3 2025"@en ;
                                       rdfs:label "Creator Engagement Report Q3 2025"@en ;
                                       dp:embedding_note "Creator Engagement Report Q3 2025 uses data product: SF Creator Insights Product."@en ,
                                                         "Creator Engagement Report Q3 2025 uses data product: SF Video Metadata Product."@en .


###  https://www.michaeldebellis.com/docs/Creator_Engagement_Report_Q3_2025_Chunk_01
docs:Creator_Engagement_Report_Q3_2025_Chunk_01 rdf:type owl:NamedIndividual ,
                                                         docs:Document_Chunk ;
                                                docs:chunk_index 1 ;
                                                docs:chunk_text "StreamForge creator engagement improved in Q3 2025, but gains were uneven across creator cohorts and upload frequencies. This report summarizes creator-side engagement metrics, highlights drivers of change, and proposes data product improvements for Q4."@en ;
                                                docs:chunk_title "Summary"@en ;
                                                rdfs:label "Creator Engagement Report Q3 2025 Chunk 01"@en .


###  https://www.michaeldebellis.com/docs/Creator_Engagement_Report_Q3_2025_Chunk_02
docs:Creator_Engagement_Report_Q3_2025_Chunk_02 rdf:type owl:NamedIndividual ,
                                                         docs:Document_Chunk ;
                                                docs:chunk_index 2 ;
                                                docs:chunk_text "Reporting period: Q3 2025 (2025-07-01 to 2025-09-30). Population: active creators with at least one upload in the last 90 days. Exclusions: policy-removed channels and test accounts."@en ;
                                                docs:chunk_title "Scope and time window"@en ;
                                                rdfs:label "Creator Engagement Report Q3 2025 Chunk 02"@en .


###  https://www.michaeldebellis.com/docs/Creator_Engagement_Report_Q3_2025_Chunk_03
docs:Creator_Engagement_Report_Q3_2025_Chunk_03 rdf:type owl:NamedIndividual ,
                                                         docs:Document_Chunk ;
                                                docs:chunk_index 3 ;
                                                docs:chunk_text "Monthly active creators (MAC): +6.2%. Uploads per active creator: +3.1%. Creator retention (90-day): +1.4 pp. Creator time-to-first-view median improved from 46 minutes to 39 minutes. Creator monetization enrollment: flat (+0.2%)."@en ;
                                                docs:chunk_title "Key metrics (Q3 vs Q2)"@en ;
                                                rdfs:label "Creator Engagement Report Q3 2025 Chunk 03"@en .


###  https://www.michaeldebellis.com/docs/Creator_Engagement_Report_Q3_2025_Chunk_04
docs:Creator_Engagement_Report_Q3_2025_Chunk_04 rdf:type owl:NamedIndividual ,
                                                         docs:Document_Chunk ;
                                                docs:chunk_index 4 ;
                                                docs:chunk_text "1) Faster time-to-first-view correlated strongly with higher creator retention, especially for small channels (<10k subscribers). 2) Improvements concentrated in long-form video; short-form creators did not see comparable lift."@en ;
                                                docs:chunk_title "Drivers and observations (1–2)"@en ;
                                                rdfs:label "Creator Engagement Report Q3 2025 Chunk 04"@en .


###  https://www.michaeldebellis.com/docs/Creator_Engagement_Report_Q3_2025_Chunk_05
docs:Creator_Engagement_Report_Q3_2025_Chunk_05 rdf:type owl:NamedIndividual ,
                                                         docs:Document_Chunk ;
                                                docs:chunk_index 5 ;
                                                docs:chunk_text "3) Metadata completeness (title, tags, category) was the strongest predictor of search impressions for new uploads. 4) The creator onboarding funnel had a measurable drop at connect payout account, but this is outside the primary scope of this report."@en ;
                                                docs:chunk_title "Drivers and observations (3–4)"@en ;
                                                rdfs:label "Creator Engagement Report Q3 2025 Chunk 05"@en .


###  https://www.michaeldebellis.com/docs/Creator_Engagement_Report_Q3_2025_Chunk_06
docs:Creator_Engagement_Report_Q3_2025_Chunk_06 rdf:type owl:NamedIndividual ,
                                                         docs:Document_Chunk ;
                                                docs:chunk_index 6 ;
                                                docs:chunk_text "Intermittent missing tag fields in the video metadata feed during August. A small fraction of creator profiles contained stale country codes after an upstream identity change. Issues did not materially change Q3 directional results, but reduce confidence in cohort segmentation."@en ;
                                                docs:chunk_title "Data quality notes"@en ;
                                                rdfs:label "Creator Engagement Report Q3 2025 Chunk 06"@en .


###  https://www.michaeldebellis.com/docs/Creator_Engagement_Report_Q3_2025_Chunk_07
docs:Creator_Engagement_Report_Q3_2025_Chunk_07 rdf:type owl:NamedIndividual ,
                                                         docs:Document_Chunk ;
                                                docs:chunk_index 7 ;
                                                docs:chunk_text "Prioritize the Video Metadata data product to improve completeness and freshness of tags and categories. Add a creator-facing metadata quality indicator. Publish a weekly Creator Engagement Snapshot. Add SLAs for metadata freshness and completeness aligned with creator experience metrics (time-to-first-view and impressions)."@en ;
                                                docs:chunk_title "Recommendations for Q4"@en ;
                                                rdfs:label "Creator Engagement Report Q3 2025 Chunk 07"@en .


###  https://www.michaeldebellis.com/docs/Creator_Engagement_Report_Q3_2025_Chunk_08
docs:Creator_Engagement_Report_Q3_2025_Chunk_08 rdf:type owl:NamedIndividual ,
                                                         docs:Document_Chunk ;
                                                docs:chunk_index 8 ;
                                                docs:chunk_text "How much of time-to-first-view improvement came from ranking changes vs metadata improvements? Can we isolate the short-form creator cohort and design targeted metadata guidance?"@en ;
                                                docs:chunk_title "Open questions"@en ;
                                                rdfs:label "Creator Engagement Report Q3 2025 Chunk 08"@en .


###  https://www.michaeldebellis.com/docs/Creator_Growth_Metric_Definition_Memo_2026
docs:Creator_Growth_Metric_Definition_Memo_2026 rdf:type owl:NamedIndividual ,
                                                         docs:Document ,
                                                         docs:Strategy_Memo ;
                                                prov:wasGeneratedBy dp:Creator_Growth_Metric_Computation_Run_2026_03_03 ;
                                                docs:has_chunk docs:Creator_Growth_Metric_Definition_Memo_2026_Chunk_01 ,
                                                               docs:Creator_Growth_Metric_Definition_Memo_2026_Chunk_02 ,
                                                               docs:Creator_Growth_Metric_Definition_Memo_2026_Chunk_03 ,
                                                               docs:Creator_Growth_Metric_Definition_Memo_2026_Chunk_04 ,
                                                               docs:Creator_Growth_Metric_Definition_Memo_2026_Chunk_05 ,
                                                               docs:Creator_Growth_Metric_Definition_Memo_2026_Chunk_06 ;
                                                docs:uses_dataset dp:SF_Creator_Insights_Dataset ;
                                                dcterms:description "Narrative memo describing the executive Creator Growth metric, how it is computed from the Creator Insights dataset, and how it should be interpreted."@en ;
                                                dcterms:title "Creator Growth Metric: Definition and Computation Notes (2026)"@en ;
                                                rdfs:label "Creator Growth Metric: Definition and Computation Notes (2026)"@en ;
                                                docs:has_topic dp:Creator_Growth_Metric_Snapshot_2026_02_08 ,
                                                               dp:SF_Creator_Insights_Dataset ;
                                                dp:embedding_note "Creator Growth Metric: Definition and Computation Notes (2026) was generated by Creator Growth Metric Computation Run (2026-03-03)."@en .


###  https://www.michaeldebellis.com/docs/Creator_Growth_Metric_Definition_Memo_2026_Chunk_01
docs:Creator_Growth_Metric_Definition_Memo_2026_Chunk_01 rdf:type owl:NamedIndividual ,
                                                                  docs:Document_Chunk ;
                                                         docs:chunk_index 1 ;
                                                         docs:chunk_text """The Creator Growth metric is an executive KPI intended to summarize whether the StreamForge creator ecosystem is expanding in a sustainable way. It is designed for high-level dashboards and strategic reporting, not for diagnosing individual creator performance.

The metric is sensitive to both creator supply (how many creators are producing content and reaching engagement thresholds) and audience demand (whether viewers are engaging with creator content). It should be interpreted alongside supporting KPIs such as retention, new creator onboarding, and content category mix."""@en ;
                                                         docs:chunk_title "What the metric is for"@en .


###  https://www.michaeldebellis.com/docs/Creator_Growth_Metric_Definition_Memo_2026_Chunk_02
docs:Creator_Growth_Metric_Definition_Memo_2026_Chunk_02 rdf:type owl:NamedIndividual ,
                                                                  docs:Document_Chunk ;
                                                         docs:chunk_index 2 ;
                                                         docs:chunk_text """Conceptually, Creator Growth increases when:
- more creators cross the 'active creator' threshold,
- existing creators increase their sustained engagement,
- and the distribution of engagement is not dominated by a tiny number of outliers.

A simple (illustrative) construction combines:
- count of active creators,
- median engagement per creator,
- and growth rate of creator cohorts over a reporting window.

Exact parameter values and thresholds are maintained as part of the metric specification and may evolve with governance review."""@en ;
                                                         docs:chunk_title "Definition (conceptual)"@en .


###  https://www.michaeldebellis.com/docs/Creator_Growth_Metric_Definition_Memo_2026_Chunk_03
docs:Creator_Growth_Metric_Definition_Memo_2026_Chunk_03 rdf:type owl:NamedIndividual ,
                                                                  docs:Document_Chunk ;
                                                         docs:chunk_index 3 ;
                                                         docs:chunk_text """The computation is derived from the SF Creator Insights Dataset. Required inputs include creator-level KPIs such as:
- play counts
- unique viewers
- engagement rate
- retention proxies

Because the metric is computed from aggregated creator KPIs, upstream data quality issues (missing events, broken joins) typically manifest as sudden metric discontinuities. The computation run should therefore enforce strict validation on input freshness and completeness."""@en ;
                                                         docs:chunk_title "Computation inputs"@en .


###  https://www.michaeldebellis.com/docs/Creator_Growth_Metric_Definition_Memo_2026_Chunk_04
docs:Creator_Growth_Metric_Definition_Memo_2026_Chunk_04 rdf:type owl:NamedIndividual ,
                                                                  docs:Document_Chunk ;
                                                         docs:chunk_index 4 ;
                                                         docs:chunk_text """The executive dashboard uses a reporting window aligned to business cadence (e.g., trailing 28 days). The computation run applies this window to creator KPIs, aggregates to the metric level, and publishes a snapshot.

Snapshots are versioned by date and should be treated as immutable. If a recomputation is required (e.g., backfill corrections), publish a new snapshot with a new version identifier rather than overwriting historical values."""@en ;
                                                         docs:chunk_title "Windowing and snapshot logic"@en .


###  https://www.michaeldebellis.com/docs/Creator_Growth_Metric_Definition_Memo_2026_Chunk_05
docs:Creator_Growth_Metric_Definition_Memo_2026_Chunk_05 rdf:type owl:NamedIndividual ,
                                                                  docs:Document_Chunk ;
                                                         docs:chunk_index 5 ;
                                                         docs:chunk_text """Interpretation guidelines:
- Short-term volatility may occur due to product experiments, seasonal effects, or data pipeline incidents.
- A sustained increase over multiple windows is stronger evidence of ecosystem growth.
- Compare the metric against segment-level analyses (e.g., demographics and region) to understand *where* growth is happening.

Governance note: if metric definitions change, the change must be communicated to consumers and recorded in a data contract so that historical comparisons remain meaningful."""@en ;
                                                         docs:chunk_title "Interpretation guidance"@en ;
                                                         docs:has_topic dp:Contract .


###  https://www.michaeldebellis.com/docs/Creator_Growth_Metric_Definition_Memo_2026_Chunk_06
docs:Creator_Growth_Metric_Definition_Memo_2026_Chunk_06 rdf:type owl:NamedIndividual ,
                                                                  docs:Document_Chunk ;
                                                         docs:chunk_index 6 ;
                                                         docs:chunk_text """Related analyses include:
- Play video demographics summary (Q1–Q4 2025)
- Creator Insights aggregation runbook
- Regional acquisition and retention decomposition

These documents together support RAG-style question answering such as: 'How is Creator Growth computed?', 'What data feeds the metric?', and 'What demographic shifts occurred in 2025 that may affect creator growth?'"""@en ;
                                                         docs:chunk_title "Link to related analyses"@en ;
                                                         docs:has_topic docs:Creator_Insights_Aggregation_Runbook_2026 ,
                                                                        docs:Play_Video_Demographics_Quarterly_Report_2025 .


